{"id": 225016816, "title": "A Place In The Sun star bursts into tears remembering late Jonnie Irwin almost 4 months after death", "text": "To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that supports HTML5 video Up Next Jonnie Irwin\u2019s co-star Jasmine Harman burst into tears recalling her memories with him, four months after his death. The beloved TV star and dad-of-three died aged 50 in February, having been diagnosed with lung cancer in 2020. He had initially kept his diagnosis private but decided to speak out about it in November 2022, explaining that he had been given \u2018months to live\u2019. Since his death, his wife Jessica Holmes and colleagues have paid tribute to him, and on Wednesday\u2019s Loose Women, Jasmine, who first appeared on screen with Irwin 20 years ago, spoke of the first time they met and his legacy. The 48-year-old explained that the two had met during filming in South Africa, having begun their television careers together. \u2018Looking at these old photos chokes me up actually,\u2019 she said. Jasmine has recalled first meeting Jonnie Irwin to film A Place In The Sun (Picture: Channel 4) Irwin died aged 50 in February (Picture: David Fisher/Shutterstock) Jasmine continued: \u2018It was a big break away for both of us from what we\u2019d been doing previously, going to work in television, so we didn\u2019t always film together because we were always in different countries, but we used to get together at the Place In The Sun live events, we became very good friends. \u2018Jonnie came to my wedding, he was the butt of a lot of my dad\u2019s jokes when my dad his speech, I met my husband on the show as well, and when Jonnie met Jess, his lovely wife, I just remember thinking, \u201cWow she is the one for him,\u201d and they had their lovely boys. \u2018It\u2019s really a hard time.\u2019 Jasmine burst into tears as she spoke of the difficult period grieving his death (Picture: ITV) Irwin is survived by his wife Jess and three young sons (Picture: jonnieirwintv) Jasmine spoke of wanting to learn from Irwin and cherish everyday (Picture: Channel 4) Breaking down into tears, she went on: \u2018You never know what\u2019s around the corner, and I think we can all take something from it\u2026 we can all cherish everyday and live with as much joy as possible, and that\u2019s what he did.\u2019 She went on to say that Jess wants people to keep his memory alive, adding: \u2018She\u2019s an amazing woman, but the outpouring of love for him has been amazing so I want to thank all the people who have sent messages.\u2019 After Harman\u2019s death was announced earlier this year, Jasmine penned a lengthy tribute referring to him as \u2018my partner in crime\u2019. https://www.instagram.com/p/C22w_F-Iq_s/?utm_source=ig_embed&ig_rid=9a2b1ded-f19a-4e68-80e4-93cf59a596ce In part, she wrote: \u2018Jonnie, you\u2019ve taught me so much in our time as work colleagues and as good friends. \u2018I have never admired you more than over the last few years as you\u2019ve faced life with cancer with positivity, determination and bloody mindedness. \u2018I\u2019ve never known anyone as strong as you. You have done yourself, your loved ones and all of us proud.\u2019 She concluded: \u2018The world is a little darker today without you, but I will always smile when I think of you. \u2018My partner in crime, my OG co-presenter \u2013 Jonnie, I will miss you.\u2019 Loose Women airs weekdays from 12.30pm on ITV1. Got a story? If you\u2019ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page \u2013 we\u2019d love to hear from you.", "summary": "", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/05/29/a-place-sun-star-bursts-tears-remembering-late-jonnie-irwin-20931982/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/85466491-0-image-a-7_1716985147022.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-29 12:49:00", "author": "Meghna Amin", "authors": ["Meghna Amin"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.03}